cs.CV, cs.NE, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.HC. 

The paper focuses on comparing the recognition performance and neural representations of adversarial images in deep neural networks and the human brain, specifically in the context of visual tasks. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). Additionally, the paper also discusses the hierarchical correspondence between the two systems, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also discusses the limitations of current DNNs, which could place it in cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction).
